   REMEDIES: When Supplements Cause Sleeplessness 

   Doctors whose patients are having trouble falling asleep or staying awake should ask what herbal medications they may be taking, researchers from the University of Illinois at Chicago report.
   The herb is called ephedra, or ma huang, and it comes from a shrublike plant grown widely in Asia.
 &UR; (Distributed by The New York Times Syndicate) &LR;  &QL; 
   If you grab an energy-boosting bar or drink for a quick lift, you might get more than you expect.
